<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 16 at 11:59PM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>Patchy black ice development overnight with temperatures hovering
in the upper 20s to around freezing, allowing for freezing of
condensation on surfaces. This will be most prevalent in valley
locations, sheltered from the winds.
Walkways and any untreated surfaces in these areas may be
slippery. If driving overnight, please use extreme caution,
especially on bridges, overpasses, and around curves. Allow plenty
of stopping distance and avoid braking suddenly.</description>
